eu.greenlightning.hypercubepdf.layout

Interface HCPLayoutResults

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HCPEmptyLayoutResults

    public interface HCPLayoutResults
    An iterator over the results of a layout process.

    Each new instance starts before the first result. The availability of more results can be checked using hasNext(). After checking that a next result exists, it can safely be activated using the next() method and its properties can then be queried using the getXXX() methods of this class. This allows to iterate over the results using this simple algorithm: 

     
     HCPLayoutResults results = ...;
     while (results.hasNext()) {
         results.next();
         ...
         result.getIndex();
         etc.
         ...
     }
    In case the results instance contains no results, the first call to next returns false and the code inside the while loop is never executed.

        int getIndex()
        Returns the index of the element that the current result deals with.

        the index of the element of the current result
